00:05:13.639 --> 00:05:18.110
is lacking the pretty much everything else.
In order to get metal for tools or stone for

00:05:18.110 --> 00:05:23.110
sculptures or wood for burning, Mesopotamia
had to trade. This trading eventually led

00:05:23.110 --> 00:05:27.689
Mesopotamia to develop the world's first
territorial kingdom, which will become very

00:05:27.689 --> 00:05:31.979
important and will eventually culminate in
some extraordinarily inbred Hapsburgs.

00:05:31.979 --> 00:05:36.520
So the city state period in Mesopotamia ended
around 2,000 BCE, probably because drought

00:05:36.520 --> 00:05:40.990
and a shift in the course of rivers led to
pastoral nomads coming in and conquering the

00:05:40.990 --> 00:05:44.939
environmentally weakened cities. And then
the nomads settled into cities of their own

00:05:44.939 --> 00:05:48.569
as nomads almost always will unless—wait
for it—

00:05:48.569 --> 00:05:50.929
...You are the Mongols.

00:05:51.780 --> 00:05:56.060
These new Mesopotamian city states were similar
to their predecessors in that they had temples

00:05:56.060 --> 00:06:00.779
and writing and their own self-glorifying stories
but they were different in some important ways.

00:06:00.779 --> 00:06:04.789
First, that early proto-socialism was replaced
by something that looked a lot like private

00:06:04.789 --> 00:06:08.520
enterprise, where people could produce as
much as they would like as long as they gave

00:06:08.520 --> 00:06:13.169
a cut, also known as taxes to the government.
We talk a lot of smack about taxes but it

00:06:13.169 --> 00:06:16.069
turns out they're pretty important to creating
stable social orders.

00:06:16.069 --> 00:06:19.440
Things were also different politically because
the dudes who'd been the tribal chiefs became

00:06:19.440 --> 00:06:24.719
like full-blown kings, who tried to extend
their power outside of cities and also tried

00:06:24.719 --> 00:06:26.939
to pass on their power to their sons.

00:06:26.939 --> 00:06:30.779
The most famous of these early monarchs is
Hammurabi or as I remember him from my high

00:06:30.779 --> 00:06:35.669
